At this point, his methods, basketball ideology, recruiting habits, and distinct offensive style have become very familiar in Ann Arbor; even though there legitimate questions about his recruiting and his typically poor defenses, he’s one of the best offensive minds in college hoops.
Each of the starters from last year’s team will be back.
While Michigan’s an undersized team, it wouldn’t be impossible for them to cobble together an adequate defense.
The offense should be better than it’s been the last two seasons, but it probably won’t come close to the fire-breathing Burke- and Stauskas-led attacks of earlier in Beilein’s tenure.
At worst, the offense will be pretty good – something that can’t be said of the defense.
